properties.Name: RfidStandard
properties.Description:
The RFID standard utilized by the Assets RFID tag device.

RFID tags can be thought of as bar codes with communications abilities.

RFID's contain a tiny transponder that, when it comes within distance of a reader, transmits its unique identifier, which can be matched to a database.

Ex:
- Gen 2
- ANSI/NCITS T6 256-2001 Radio Frequency Identification (RFID) Tech 
- TC 104 / SC 4 Identification and communication
- ISO 6346 
- JTC 1/SC 31 Automatic Identification and Data Capture Techniques
- JTC 1/SC 17 Identification Cards and related devices

Columns.Name: RfidStandardId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a RFID Standard.

Columns.Name: RfidStandardName
Columns.Description: The name of a RFID Standard.

Columns.Name: RfidStandardDescription
Columns.Description: The description of a RFID Standard.
